The insect order Trichoptera (caddisflies) is composed of species whose eggs, larvae, and pupae are particularly abundant and diverse in freshwater, whereas their adults are generally terrestrial. Most caddisflies species have one generation per year (univoltine) and are egg-laying (oviparous) (
Morse et al. 2019
). Larvae of the different species can live under many different ecological conditions and habitats (
García et al. 2006
). There are more than 17,000 species worldwide (
Morse et al. 2019
).

In Morocco , the trichopterological fauna includes 85 species distributed in two suborders: The Annulipalpia include 33 species distributed over 5 families and the Integripalpia comprise 52 species divided among 9 families, including the family Calamoceratidae ( Hajji 2017 ,
Mabrouki et al. 2023
).

Globally, the Calamoceratidae include 198 species in 8 genera:
Anisocentropus McLachlan 1863
;
Phylloicus Müller 1880
;
Banyallarga Navás 1916
;
Ganonema McLachlan 1866
;
Ascalaphomerus Walker 1852
;
Calamoceras Brauer 1865
;
Georgium Fischer 1964
; and
Heteroplectron McLachlan 1871
(
Holzenthal et al. 2007
; Morse unpublished data). Among these genera,
Calamoceras
is the only genus found in the West Palearctic Region and includes only two species (Graff et al. 2008):
Calamoceras marsupus Brauer 1865
and
Calamoceras illiesi Malicky & Kumanski 1974
.
Calamoceras marsupus
occurs in France , the Iberic-Macaronesian region, the Pyrenees, the Western Highlands, the Western Plains (Graff et al. 2008), and Morocco ( Tayoub 1989 ; El Alami & Dakki 1998 ;
Bonada et al. 2008
;
Hajji et al. 2013
;
El Bazi et al. 2017
; Hajji 2017 ;
Guellaf et al. 2021
) and has a preference for intermittent watercourses (
Guellec et al. 2016
).
Calamoceras illiesi
occurs in Bulgaria ( Kumanski 1988 ), Croatia , Greece ( Malicky 2005 ), Turkey ( Sipahiler 2005 ), and the western and southern Caucasus ( Ivanov 2011 ).

